    {
      "paragraph_name": "PASFLPCB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This copybook defines the structure of the PASFLPCB data area, which is likely used for communication between a COBOL program and the IMS database system. The PASFLPCB contains information about the database, segment level, PCB status, processing options, segment name, key feedback length, number of sensitive segments, and the key feedback area itself. The PASFL-DBDNAME (line 18) specifies the database name. The PASFL-SEG-LEVEL (line 19) indicates the segment level. PASFL-PCB-STATUS (line 20) provides the status of the PCB. PASFL-PCB-PROCOPT (line 21) defines the processing options. PASFL-SEG-NAME (line 23) stores the name of the segment. PASFL-KEYFB-NAME (line 24) and PASFL-NUM-SENSEGS (line 25) appear to be related to key feedback information. PASFL-KEYFB (line 26) is a 100-byte field that likely holds the key feedback data. This copybook is intended to be included in COBOL programs that interact with IMS databases to access and manipulate data.",
